Sentencas: The cathode reaction mechanism of porous Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta, a mixed ionic and electronic conductor (MIEC), is studied through a comparison with the composite cathode Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: First, the cathodic behaviour of porous Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 are observed for micro-structure and impedance spectra according to Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 addition.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells
Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathode reaction mechanism is discussed in terms of frequency response, activation energy.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: reaction order and electrode resistance for different oxygen partial pressures p(O-2) at various temperatures.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three elementary steps are considered to be involved in the cathodic reaction: (i) oxygen ion transfer at the cathode-electrolyte interface; (ii) oxygen ion conduction in the bulk cathode; (iii) gas phase diffusion of oxygen.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A reaction model based on the empirical equivalent circuit is introduced and analyzed using the impedance spectra.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode resistance at high frequency (R-c.HF) in the impedance spectra represents reaction steps (i), due to its fast reaction rate.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode resistance at high frequency is independent of p(O-2) at a constant temperature because the semicircle of R-c.HF in the complex plane of the impedance spectra is held constant for different values of p(O-2).
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Reaction steps (ii) and (iii) are the dominant processes for a MIEC cathode, according to the analysis results.
Titulo: Cathode reaction mechanism of porous-structured Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ and Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The proposed cathode reaction model and results for a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) well describe a MIEC cathode with high ionic conductivity, and assist the understanding of the MIEC cathode reaction mechanism.
